    "author": "@Sourav-b9m",
    "author_channel_id": "UCgFybj-lpUSyr0MsmxGCM5g",
    "text": "I have a 1000kv delta configuration bldc motor. I want to run it with 5-12v 50hz transformer. Motor's phase to phase resistance is 0.24ohm. \nWhat will be the running capacitor value?\nPlease help",
    "likes": 2,
    "published_at": "2025-07-23T23:13:33Z",
    "reply_count": 2,
    "replies": [
      {
        "id": "UgzAoi_uSw87h7Neci94AaABAg.AKwU8Qbv27IAKwWGWsyCKo",
        "author": "@ThinkingandTinkering",
        "author_channel_id": "UC4AkVj-qnJxNtKuz3rkq16A",
        "text": "you don't need a running capacitor with a BLDC motor you can use a link capacitor if you want and the rule of thumb is 2 microfarads per watt - or at least that is my memory of it",
        "likes": 2,
        "published_at": "2025-07-23T23:32:08Z"
      },
      {
        "id": "UgzAoi_uSw87h7Neci94AaABAg.AKwU8Qbv27IAKwWe1b22Ss",
        "author": "@Sourav-b9m",
        "author_channel_id": "UCgFybj-lpUSyr0MsmxGCM5g",
        "text": "Thank you so much sir​@ThinkingandTinkering",
        "likes": 1,
        "published_at": "2025-07-23T23:35:29Z"
      }
    ]
